a1BZi4g==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating resource loading**\\n\\nI'm thinking through the resource loading situation here. If there’s no parent resource, then getResource would return null, which means I can still reach that line of code. I realize I can assert null to check for a shadow. We might need a URL for creation; options include a data URL or using getClass().getClassLoader to access the resource path. However, I need to ensure the child and parent resource have the same name for stability. It's a bit tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading**\\n\\nI'm diving into the details of class loading with the parent override. I see that with a custom ClassLoader, I can define a method to get the resource. If the expected resource is found, I can return it; otherwise, I might call the superclass method. This leads me to think about how to utilize the ChildFirst strategy for loading classes using Class.forName. I could also use loader.loadClass(name) to handle it directly. It's quite a puzzle!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java compatibility**\\n\\nI'm contemplating the existing style of coding, starting with static, then moving to Java, and finally to org. I wonder if I'll need java.util.LinkedHashMap or if Map.of is sufficient. Since I'm considering Java 21, I’m questioning whether I need to ensure compatibility with source code from Java 11. However, using Map.of is already okay from Java 9, so maybe I just need to check that too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OoiuRMZRNkFLJlTU6YFt1LSX|fc_0e66c840c759112b016a254f9bd6048195aa99d2de2fbadbbb", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_modelmapper.modelmapper;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.modelmapper.ModelMapper;\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.description.type.TypeDescription;\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.DynamicType;\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.ChildFirst;\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.PersistenceHandler;\n\npublic class ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_PACKAGE = \"org_modelmapper.modelmapper.generated\";\n    private static final String STATIC_LOAD_TYPE_NAME = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \".ChildFirstStaticLoadType\";\n    private static final String MANIFEST_TYPE_NAME = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \".ChildFirstManifestType\";\n    private static final String LATENT_TYPE_NAME = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \".ChildFirstLatentType\";\n    private static final String MODELMAPPER_RESOURCE = \"org/modelmapper/ModelMapper.class\";\n\n    @Test\n    void staticLoadDefinesGeneratedTypesThroughChildFirstLoader() {\n        try {\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloadedType = makeUnloaded(STATIC_LOAD_TYPE_NAME);\n            TypeDescription typeDescription = unloadedType.getTypeDescription();\n\n            Map<TypeDescription, Class<?>> loadedTypes = ChildFirst.load(\n                    testClassLoader(),\n                    Map.of(typeDescription, unloadedType.getBytes()));\n\n            Class<?> loadedType = loadedTypes.get(typeDescription);\n            assertThat(loadedType).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(loadedType.getName()).isEqualTo(STATIC_LOAD_TYPE_NAME);\n            assertThat(loadedType.getClassLoader()).isInstanceOf(ChildFirst.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void manifestPersistenceServesGeneratedClassResourcesAndDelegatesToParentResources()\n            throws IOException {\n        try {\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloadedType = makeUnloaded(MANIFEST_TYPE_NAME);\n            String generatedResourceName = resourceName(MANIFEST_TYPE_NAME);\n            ChildFirst classLoader = new ChildFirst(\n                    testClassLoader(),\n                    Map.of(MANIFEST_TYPE_NAME, unloadedType.getBytes()),\n                    PersistenceHandler.MANIFEST);\n\n            URL generatedResource = classLoader.getResource(generatedResourceName);\n            assertThat(generatedResource).isNotNull();\n\n            URL parentResource = classLoader.getResource(MODELMAPPER_RESOURCE);\n            assertThat(parentResource).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(parentResource).isEqualTo(testClassLoader().getResource(MODELMAPPER_RESOURCE));\n\n            List<URL> parentResources = Collections.list(classLoader.getResources(MODELMAPPER_RESOURCE));\n            assertThat(parentResources).isNotEmpty();\n\n            List<URL> generatedResources = Collections.list(\n                    classLoader.getResources(generatedResourceName));\n            assertThat(generatedResources).isNotEmpty();\n            assertThat(generatedResources.get(0)).isEqualTo(generatedResource);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void latentLoadedClassResourceShadowsParentResourceWithSameName()\n            throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        try {\n            DynamicType.Unloaded<?> unloadedType = makeUnloaded(LATENT_TYPE_NAME);\n            String generatedResourceName = resourceName(LATENT_TYPE_NAME);\n            URL parentResource = ModelMapper.class.getResource(\"ModelMapper.class\");\n            ClassLoader parentClassLoader = new ResourceOnlyClassLoader(\n                    testClassLoader(),\n                    generatedResourceName,\n                    parentResource);\n            ChildFirst classLoader = new ChildFirst(\n                    parentClassLoader,\n                    Map.of(LATENT_TYPE_NAME, unloadedType.getBytes()),\n                    PersistenceHandler.LATENT);\n\n            Class<?> loadedType = classLoader.loadClass(LATENT_TYPE_NAME);\n            assertThat(loadedType.getName()).isEqualTo(LATENT_TYPE_NAME);\n            assertThat(loadedType.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n\n            assertThat(classLoader.getResource(generatedResourceName)).isNull();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static DynamicType.Unloaded<?> makeUnloaded(String typeName) {\n        return new ByteBuddy()\n                .subclass(Object.class)\n                .name(typeName)\n                .make();\n    }\n\n    private static ClassLoader testClassLoader() {\n        return ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest.class.getClassLoader();\n    }\n\n    private static String resourceName(String typeName) {\n        return typeName.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceOnlyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final String resourceName;\n        private final URL resource;\n\n        private ResourceOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, String resourceName, URL resource) {\n            super(parent);\n            this.resourceName = resourceName;\n            this.resource = resource;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String name) {\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\n                return resource;\n            }\n            return super.getResource(name);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration<URL> getResources(String name) throws IOException {\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\n                return Collections.enumeration(List.of(resource));\n            }\n            return super.getResources(name);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_modelmapper.modelmapper;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.net.URL;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.Map;\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.modelmapper.ModelMapper;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.description.type.TypeDescription;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.DynamicType;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.ChildFirst;\\nimport org.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader.PersistenceHandler;\\n\\npublic class ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerChildFirstTest {\\n    private static final String GENERATED_PACKAGE = \\\"org_modelmapper.modelmapper.generated\\\";\\n    private static final String STATIC_LOAD_TYPE_NAME = GENERATED_PACKAGE + \\\".ChildFirstStaticLoadType\\\";\\n    private static final String M